fix: Tauri app stuck on 'loading' after server restart. The SPA had no recovery mechanism — if the sidecar restarted, all in-memory state was stale and API calls failed silently. Added a connection health monitor in +layout.svelte that polls /api/agents every 5s with a 3s timeout. If the server goes unreachable (wasDisconnected=true) then comes back, triggers window.location.reload() to reset all SPA state. Shows a 'Reconnecting...' overlay with z-index 200 (above everything including Docker modal) while disconnected.
